'''Nicholas 'Nick' Hammond''' is an English [[ornithology|ornithologist]] and author, and a former director of the [[Wildlife Trust for Bedfordshire, Cambridgeshire and Northamptonshire]].<ref name="ISoaT">{{cite web|url=http://www.wildlifetrusts.org/events/2013/04/24/search-tiger|title=In Search of a Tiger|publisher=[[The Wildlife Trusts]]|accessdate=6 November 2013}}</ref> He was editor of the [[Royal Society for the Protection of Birds]]' ''Birds'' magazine, and later its director of communications. He has written a number of books on, and speaks about, wildlife art.<ref name="RSPBLichfield">{{cite web|url=http://www.rspb.org.uk/groups/lichfield/events/|title=Lichfield & District Local Group - Events|publisher=The [[Royal Society for the Protection of Birds]]|accessdate=6 November 2013}}</ref>

== RSPB ==

Hammond undertook three stints as editor of the Royal Society for the Protection of Birds (RSPB) magazine ''Birds'', from volume 1 number 7 – vol. 5 no. 5 (November/December 1966—September/October 1974); vol. 6 no. 6 – vol. 6 no. 9 (Spring-Winter  1977) and vol. 10 no. 3 – vol. 11 no. 1 (Autumn 1984-Spring 1986).<ref name ="Birds">Credited in each issue</ref> He also served as the charity's director of communications.<ref name="Fox">{{Cite journal |last= Fox |first= Larry |author2=Barbara Radin Fox |title= Castles, volcanoes, carnival - oh, my! |journal= Chicago Sun-Times |accessdate= 2013-11-06 |date= 1998-06-07 |url= http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-4448369.html |via=[[HighBeam]] |subscription=yes}}</ref>

