{{Mesopotamian myth|expanded=3}}

'''Uraš''' or '''Urash''', in [[Sumerian mythology]], is a goddess of earth, and one of the consorts of the sky god [[Anu]]. She is the mother of the goddess [[Ninsun]] and a grandmother of the [[hero]] [[Gilgamesh]].

However, ''Uras'' may only have been another name for [[Antum]], Anu's wife.<ref name="Horowitz1998">{{cite book|author=Wayne Horowitz|title=Mesopotamian Cosmic Geography|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=P8fl8BXpR0MC&pg=PA231|date=1 January 1998|publisher=Eisenbrauns|isbn=978-0-931464-99-7|pages=231–}}</ref> The name ''Uras'' even became applied to Anu himself, and acquired the meaning "heaven".<ref name="Horowitz1998"/> [[Ninurta]] also was apparently called ''Uras'' in later times.<ref name="BlackGreen1992">{{cite book|author1=Jeremy Black|author2=Anthony Green|title=Gods, Demons and Symbols of Ancient Mesopotamia: An Illustrated Dictionary|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pr8-i1iFnIQC&pg=PA182|year=1992|publisher=University of Texas Press|isbn=978-0-292-70794-8|pages=182–}}</ref>

